                            <comment id="232733" author="jonbut" created="Wed, 29 Aug 2018 13:51:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I spoke with someone from Cluster Labs and they say:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
ocf:lustre:Lustre is an
agent provided by the lustre organization. All agents included in the resource-agents project are under the heartbeat provider. So my guess would be
that you need to install the agent through a &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; provided by the Lustre
project.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I can confirm I have been able to use this resource agent with both this version and a previous version. Maybe there is a package I need to install which will contain the resource?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="232724" author="pjones" created="Wed, 29 Aug 2018 12:20:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The instructions on lustre.org are more likely to be reflecting the current LTS releases (2.10.x) - that&apos;s quite an old version that you are running. For general how-to questions I suggest that you post them on the lustre-discuss mailing list - &lt;a href=&quot;http://lists.lustre.org/listinfo.cgi/lustre-discuss-lustre.org&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://lists.lustre.org/listinfo.cgi/lustre-discuss-lustre.org&lt;/a&gt;&#160;Tickets in the issue tracking system are to track fixes/activities for future releases and so get reviewed less often.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
